      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model selection justified relative to flow regime; sensitivity to model form documented.",
      "rationale": "Model form credibility was evaluated through a comprehensive qualitative assessment of turbulence closure selection for the transitional flow regime present in the centrifugal pump (Re ~ 3,000–8,000). The SST k-omega model was selected based on its established performance in rotating machinery with adverse pressure gradients, as documented in peer-reviewed literature (Wieghardt benchmark, Menter 1994). Sensitivity runs comparing k-epsilon realizable and SST k-omega showed hemolysis index differences of less than 4% across all operating points, confirming that the model form is not a dominant source of uncertainty for this QoI. Expert review by two independent fluid dynamics specialists confirmed the appropriateness of the turbulence model for this application. The qualitative weight of evidence — literature precedent, expert judgment, and sensitivity analysis — collectively supports high confidence in the selected model form for the CPB hemolysis COU."
    },
